name: Yakima County Health District COVID Vaccination Site
notes: ***1st & 2nd DOSE PFIZER VACCINATIONS!!!!***!!!!VACUNAS DE PRIMERA Y SEGUNDA DOSIS PFIZER!!! The vaccination clinic will take place at the Toppenish Flea Market. Masks are required. Please wear clothing which allows access to your shoulder. Vaccinations at this site are reserved for people who live and/or work in Washington State. All individuals 12 and over are eligible to get vaccinated. Those under 18 must be accompanied by a parent/guardian or must get parental consent via video/phone call or paper format. La clínica de vacunación se ubicará en La Pulga de Toppenish. Se requieren máscaras. Por favor, use ropa que permita acceso a su brazo. Las vacunas en este sitio están reservadas para las personas que viven o trabajan en el estado de Washington. Todas las personas mayores de 12 años son elegibles para vacunarse. Los menores de 18 años deben estar acompañados por un padre/tutor o deben obtener el consentimiento de los padres por video/llamada telefónica o en papel. ***1st & 2nd DOSE PFIZER VACCINATIONS!!!!***!!!!VACUNAS DE PRIMERA Y SEGUNDA DOSIS PFIZER!!!
If you are signing up for a second dose, you must get the same vaccine brand as your first dose.

name: Thurston County Public Health Medical Reserve Corp
notes: This is a Pfizer vaccination event for anyone age 12 and older. This is a walk-in clinic at the Regional Athletic Center (RAC), 8345 Steilacoom Rd SE, Olympia, WA 98513, for anyone age 12 and older from 11am-4pm. All minors 12 to 17 years old must receive parent or guardian consent to receive a COVID-19 vaccine. This must be done in PrepMod when registering for an appointment. Parents or guardians do not have to be present at the time of vaccination if they signed the consent form online during registration. • Please bring a form of identification with you to your appointment - ID card, passport, or other document with your name and birthday on it. • Wear a short-sleeved shirt, but dress with layers if necessary. • Waiting at least 15 minutes after vaccination is required.
If you are signing up for a second dose, you must get the same vaccine brand as your first dose.

name: Walla Walla Mobile Units
notes:
Walla Walla Food Truck Night at Burwood Brewing Company!

Providence Population Health Team and their Mobile Outreach Service Team (MOST Bus) will be in attendance at the August 9th Food Truck Night! 

Their team will be offering COVID-19 Vaccines (Pfizer, Moderna, and Johnson & Johnson). 

PFIZER vaccinations are available for all qualifying individuals aged 12 years & over. Parental/Guardian consent is required for those 12 – 17 years old; parent/guardian consent and signature can be completed on-site or in the final screen of the online registration process.

MODERNA and JOHNSON & JOHNSON vaccinations are available for people 18 years and older.

Preregistration is recommended but not required. Walk-up’s are welcome!
*****************************************************************
¡Noche de camiones de comida de Walla Walla en Burwood Brewing Company!

¡El Equipo de Salud de la Población de Providence y su Equipo de Servicio de Alcance Móvil (MOST Bus) asistirán a la Noche de Camiones de Comida del 9 de agosto!

Su equipo ofrecerá vacunas COVID-19 (Pfizer, Moderna y Johnson & Johnson).

Las vacunas PFIZER están disponibles para todas las personas calificadas mayores de 12 años. Se requiere el consentimiento de los padres / tutores para las personas de 12 a 17 años; El consentimiento y la firma del padre / tutor se puede completar en el sitio o en la pantalla final del proceso de registro en línea.

Las vacunas MODERNA y JOHNSON & JOHNSON están disponibles para personas mayores de 18 años.

Se recomienda el registro previo, pero no es obligatorio. ¡Los walk-up son bienvenidos!
If you are signing up for a second dose, you must get the same vaccine brand as your first dose.
